**Critical streaming UX detail**: When `content_block_delta` events arrive with `text_delta`, we accumulate the text and re-render the full accumulated text through `marked.parse()` into the current text element. This gives proper markdown rendering even mid-stream. However, re-parsing markdown on every token would be expensive. The solution: use `requestAnimationFrame` to batch updates -- accumulate deltas synchronously, but only call `marked.parse()` + DOM update at most once per frame (roughly 60fps). This gives smooth streaming without jank.

**Final message replacement**: When the `assistant` event arrives with the complete `message.content[]`, replace the streamed content with a clean re-render of the final text. This ensures markdown is perfectly rendered (streaming can cause transient artifacts, e.g., an incomplete code fence).

